cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it investigates the role of structural diversity on retention in online social networking platforms. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses social network analysis to study user behavior on Twitter. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) as it involves altering network recommendations for new users, which could have implications for security. The paper also touches upon human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it studies user engagement on social networking platforms, and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves analyzing large-scale data sets.
